Prerequisite of CMPE 207 is completing CMPE 206 (Computer Network Design) or equivalent and its for students who are Proficient in C/C++, UNIX/Linux.

Prerequisite of CMPE 226 is completing CMPE 272 first or having instructor's consent. It is for Computer Engineering or Software Engineering majors only and for students having Java development, general relational database (JDBC) proficiency, OOA/D, UML and software engineering concepts/experience.
Prerequisite of CMPE 255 is being Classified graduate or instructor's consent for non-MS SE majors.
Prerequisite of CMPE 272 - Enterprise SW Platforms is being a Classified student or having Instructor’s consent.
Prerequisite of CMPE 274 is completing CMPE 272 and CMPE 273 first or having instructor's consent.
Prerequisite of CMPE 275 is completing CMPE 273 first or instructor's consent. This course is available for Computer Engineering and Software Engineering majors only.
Prerequisite of CMPE 277 is being Classified graduate or having instructor's consent. It requires students to be proficient in Java programming language(OOP).
Prerequisite of CMPE 280 is being Classified graduate or having instructor's consent. This course is available for Computer Engineering and Software Engineering majors only.
Prerequisite of CMPE 281 - Cloud Technologies course is completion of CMPE 272 or if you get lucky, instructor's consent.
Prerequisite of CMPE 282 is completing CMPE 281 - Cloud Computing first or having instructor's consent.
